<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Dissolved Oxygen Measurement</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary: #2F4F4F;
            --primary-light: #3a5f5f;
            --secondary: #778899;
            --accent: #20B2AA;
            --light-bg: #f5f5f5;
            --dark-text: #2d3748;
            --border-color: #e0e0e0;
            --white: #ffffff;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: var(--light-bg);
            color: var(--dark-text);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 30px;
            background: var(--white);
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0px 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        h1 {
            color: var(--primary);
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
            padding-bottom: 10px;
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        .info-section {
            margin-top: 30px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #e3f2fd;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--primary);
            border-radius: 0 5px 5px 0;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        .info-section p:last-child {
            margin-bottom: 0;
        }

        .btn {
            display: block;
            margin: 25px auto;
            padding: 12px 25px;
            background-color: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 1rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
        }

        .btn:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-light);
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }

        /* Back button */
        .back-button-container {
            position: fixed;
            top: 20px;
            left: 20px;
            z-index: 1000;
        }

        .back-button {
            background-color: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 5px;
        }

        .back-button:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-light);
            transform: translateX(-3px);
        }

        /* Highlight important terms */
        .highlight {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--primary);
        }

        .feature-list {
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        .feature-list li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .definition-box {
            background-color: #e1f5fe;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            border-radius: 0 5px 5px 0;
        }

        .definition-title {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--primary);
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .sensor-image {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 500px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            display: block;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        }

        .formula {
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            background-color: #f5f5f5;
            padding: 8px 12px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            display: inline-block;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }

        /* Responsive design */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .container {
                margin: 15px;
                padding: 20px;
            }
            
            h1 {
                font-size: 1.8rem;
            }
            
            .back-button-container {
                position: relative;
                top: auto;
                left: auto;
                margin-bottom: 15px;
            }
            
            .back-button {
                position: relative;
                margin: 0 auto 20px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Back to Home Button -->
    <div class="back-button-container">
        <button class="back-button" onclick="goBackHome()">&#8592; Back to Parameters</button>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>Dissolved Oxygen (DO) Measurement</h1>
        
        <div class="definition-box">
            <div class="definition-title">Dissolved Oxygen (DO)</div>
            <p>The concentration of molecular oxygen (Oâ‚‚) dissolved in water, essential for aquatic life and a key indicator of water quality and ecosystem health.</p>
        </div>

        <p>DO levels are critical for maintaining healthy aquatic ecosystems and are influenced by physical, chemical, and biological factors in the water column.</p>

        <button class="btn" onclick="toggleInfo()">Show Measurement Details</button>
        
        <div class="info-section" id="moreInfo" style="display: none;">
            <h2>Sources and Significance</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Atmospheric exchange:</span> Oxygen dissolves at the air-water interface</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Photosynthesis:</span> Primary production by aquatic plants and algae</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Ecological importance:</span>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Essential for fish and aquatic organism respiration</li>
                        <li>Critical for aerobic decomposition of organic matter</li>
                        <li>Indicator of water quality and pollution levels</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <img src="images/do-sensor.jpg" alt="Dissolved oxygen measurement sensor" class="sensor-image">

            <h2>Measurement Technologies</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Electrochemical sensors:</span>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Clark-type (polarographic) sensors</li>
                        <li>Galvanic sensors</li>
                        <li>Require membrane replacement and electrolyte refills</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Optical sensors:</span>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Fluorescence-based measurement</li>
                        <li>No membranes or electrolytes required</li>
                        <li>Minimal maintenance</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Winkler titration:</span> Traditional laboratory method (chemical analysis)</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Factors Affecting DO Levels</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Temperature:</span> Inverse relationship (colder water holds more oxygen)</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Salinity:</span> Decreases oxygen solubility</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Altitude/Barometric Pressure:</span> Lower pressure reduces solubility</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Biological activity:</span>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Photosynthesis (produces oxygen during daylight)</li>
                        <li>Respiration (consumes oxygen continuously)</li>
                        <li>Decomposition (consumes oxygen)</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Typical DO Ranges</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Healthy waters:</span> 6-10 mg/L (varies with temperature)</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Stressful for aquatic life:</span> 2-4 mg/L</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Lethal conditions:</span> Below 2 mg/L</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Supersaturation:</span> Can exceed 20 mg/L during algal blooms</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Calibration and Maintenance</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Zero calibration:</span> In oxygen-free solution (sodium sulfite)</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Span calibration:</span> In air-saturated water or known standard</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Maintenance:</span>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Membrane replacement for electrochemical sensors</li>
                        <li>Optical cap replacement for optical sensors</li>
                        <li>Regular cleaning to prevent biofouling</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Applications</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Aquatic ecosystem monitoring</li>
                <li>Wastewater treatment process control</li>
                <li>Aquaculture management</li>
                <li>Industrial discharge monitoring</li>
                <li>Scientific research</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        function goBackHome() {
            window.location.href = 'parameters';
        }

        function toggleInfo() {
            const info = document.getElementById("moreInfo");
            const button = document.querySelector(".btn");
            
            if (info.style.display === "none") {
                info.style.display = "block";
                button.textContent = "Hide Measurement Details";
            } else {
                info.style.display = "none";
                button.textContent = "Show Measurement Details";
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>